Contribution of propylene glycol-induced Heinz body formation to anemia in cats. Propylene glycol (PG) is a common preservative and source of synthetic carbohydrates in soft-moist pet foods. Propylene glycol was fed to cats for 5 weeks at concentrations found in commercial diets (1.6 g/kg of body weight 12% of diet on a dry-weight basis) and for 3 weeks at concentrations exceeding usual intake (8 g/kg